In March 2007, the Bank received a one time allocation of $8.6 million in overhead.  Effective 4/1/07, the Bank has entered into an agreement with its parent which states that the parent agrees not to allocate any overhead to the Bank until its net income, after allocation, exceeds $2 million for a period of three years. Legg Mason Investment Counsel & Trust Company, NA ("Bank") now assesses and monitors its capital, capital needs and liquidity on a quarterly basis through its Investment Policy Committee. The Income & Expense sheet, Balance Sheet and Tier 1 Capital is reviewed monthly.  The Investment Policy Committee minutes are submitted to the Board of Directors.  In addition, as part of the quarterly financial review, the Bank's capital and liquidity will be reviewed by the Board.

The implementation of this accounting principal reguires the Bank to reclassify that porition of non credit losses associated with investment securities recorded through the income statement in 2008, out of beginning retained earnings on January 1, 2009 and into other comprehensive income.  All subsequent credit losses on the securities are to be reported and recorded throght the income statement when the losses are determinable based on the discounted expected cash fllow of the security.
